body:
### expected behaviour
i should be able to create a new file from within the oc web interface, even if the storage space i'm accessing is a remote smb share (accessing with an ldap user that has full read/write access to that share).

### actual behaviour
the file is not created on the remote smb share. when i create the file the web interface lists the file name in the directory but if i click on it i get an owncloud error. if i open the smb share with, eg. windows file explorer, i can confirm that the file was not created.

### steps to reproduce
1. open oc web interface and add an external smb share (use user with full read/write access)
2. create new folder (optional but at least shows that it works fine)
3. create a new text file (the file name should be displayed in the web inrterface but you should notice that it isn't created in the filesystem)
4. try to open the file from the web interface and get an error message such as "cloud not found /username/testfolder/newfolder/newfile.txt"

### server configuration
operating system: gentoo linux kernel 2.6.36

web server: apache 2.2.24

database: mysql 5.1.67

php version: 5.4.13

owncloud version: 5.0.10

### client configuration
browser: firefox 22.0

operating system: windows 7

